    If $(D !!value) is true, $(D value) is returned. Otherwise,
    $(D new ErrnoException(msg)) is thrown. $(D ErrnoException) assumes that the
    last operation set $(D errno) to an error code.

    Example:
    --------------------
    auto f = errnoEnforce(fopen("data.txt"));
    auto line = readln(f);
